Tile ControlNet + Detail Tweaker LoRA + Upscale = More details

items.name: Nike Air Command Force
items.description:
Nike Air Command Force

If there is a sneaker that screams 1990's era basketball then this is it. The Nike Air Command Force is an iconic high-top sneaker and this LoRA allows you to put a part of sneaker history in your own generations.

Usage

Either just add the LoRA to your prompt or use commandforce as trigger word for a stronger effect. If you desire a certain colorway you can use one of the following:

  • volt commandforce

  • ultramarine commandforce

  • red commandforce

  • jade commandforce

  • black commandforce

Some colorways (like the black one) are a bit more difficult to obtain, so you might need to try different weights or prompts with these.

Infos

The LoRA was trained on SD 1.5 as base model with 150 images, but works well on either realistic or anime models and can also be used very well for NSFW creations. Recommended strength is 1. Unfortunately color bleed is pretty strong with this LoRA, so be warned that often you'll get matching sneaker, shirt and hair colors.

items.name: Weight Difference - Slim with Fat
items.description:
This LoHa is designed to make it easier to generate characters with a large difference in body fat. General purpose models don't make fat characters well, and models specifically for making fat characters can often make all characters in the image fat. Tags such as 'size difference' often make them giant and tiny. This LoHa was trained on 272 generated images where one character is much fatter than the other, along with 90 control images with no weight difference.

The filename contains the main tags you will need: weightdifference (272) and slimwithfat (192). However, it also works with regular weight and body type tags, for instance "skinny, fat, big belly". Other trained tags to tweak your output: skinnywithfat (70), chubbywithfat (80), slimwithobese (85), skinnywithobese (30), chubbywithobese (30).

It separates the concepts of different body types quite well. You can put "belly" or "chubby" in the negatives to slim down the smaller person and not affect the larger person. Adding strength to "weightdifference" will usually make the larger one take up more space.

Other good tags to play with: feeding, belly grab, grabbing from behind, sitting on lap, hand on another's stomach, hand on own stomach, love handles, shirt lift. Use with symix to make stuffing scenes.

It can do pairs and trios of boys and girls very well. For a boy and a girl together, results can vary. To avoid one partner disappearing: add tags "couple, hetero" and negative tag "solo". To increase your chances of a slim girl and fat boy: use models or loras designed for making males, like allboymix. To increase your chances of a slim boy and fat girl: use models and loras designed for making fat females, like chubbygirlsgolden and symix, use tags like "long hair, large breasts, wide hips"

I hope this is helpful for people! If you run into problems or have suggestions for future versions of the lora, please let me know. I plan to improve it in the future.

items.name: Vulcan
items.description:
Hi again and welcome to Vulcan!


"Vulcan" is part of my brand new and personal color series where I aim to create an overall style but oriented mostly for certain color aesthetics so it can be used for characters, objects, landscapes, etc. This time is the turn of red/yellow dominance.

"Vulcan" aims to create globalized creations but with red and yellow colors (and in this case there won't be too much derivatives except orangish) and high saturated images. This LORA is extremely good for comics, certain graphic art, posters etc.

Main token is v5lcn and class is style so you can use v5lcn Style or just v5lcn. I recommend this time the first case.

How to use this LORA?

*************************

You can refer to the sample images I upload in the post but:

- For characters a portrait of "concept" in the style of v5lcn

- For landscape and objects v5lcn style concept or a "concept" in the style of v5lcn

- You can control mono colors or influence them using "red" or "yellow" in the prompt. In most cases you will get a mix but if you want certain focus remember you can use that.

Which are the best values?

*******************************

- You can go from 0.7/0.8 onwards till 1 and 1 onwards for a more "v5lcn style".

If you are focusing a global dominance of black/red/yellow and found "annoying" colors, rise the the LORA to 1.X or try to simplify the prompt. This LORA is good with few words.

- To control the saturation is recommended to start from a CFG scale of 5 and play from there. Remember the red and yellow words. They're sub tokens.



Which models are good for this LORA?

********************************************

- Tested on 5 different models except on (as always) Realistic Vision but I'd recommend Colorful, RevAnimated, Dreamshaper... if you use anime models like Cardos mind that the style will adapt towards anime with all it's lineart area, so be careful.

This LORA is GOOD for:

******************************

- Highly saturated/contrasted art and red/yellow landscapes.
- Comic R&Y style in duotones contrasted and saturated.
- Graphic design style for your creations.
- Duotone creations with saturated and lined values.

- Saturated and high contrasted colors in general with highly R/Y dominance.

- Globalized creations (such as really anything you want). Just remember what happens
with anime models.


This LORA is NOT designed for:

***********************************

- Realistic things (maybe) since it's trained on certain drawings and illustrations. Should be difficul to guide it to a realistic basis.

IMPORTANT!

I wrote an article here and it's like my finetunning diary for the ones interested with releases upcoming, trainings done, exclusive patreon models previews, personal thoughts, etc. So if you want to see what I'm planning or what I'm into, feel free to take a look.

As always thanks to everyone reviewing, giving feedback , commenting and supportin us in Patreon. Keep supporting us so we can keep creating and delivering quality content.

David.

If you like what I do please consider supporting me on Patreon and contributing your ideas to my future projects!

Edvard Munch art style lora for SDXL 1.0. Edvard Munch was a Norwegian symbolist and expressionist painter and printmaker and now you can generate art similar to his style within your own Stable Diffusion workflow. This model was trained on 1024 x 1024 and is able to produce higher details and greater accuracy than if you were to simply type his name into your prompt.

I use this at a weight of around 1 but you may have to adjust the weight up or down to 0.8 incrementally depending on the complexity of your prompt. I used clip skip 1 for all of the images you see uploaded to this page. CFG 7 I think works good for this art style.

The main trigger is mnch and there are no additional tags for this art style. Be creative with your txt2img or use img2img to guide the basic composition and colors.

Have fun playing around with this remarkable tech and if you like it be sure to review and upload all of your amazing works of art!

items.name: Hayley Magnus
items.description:
Hayley Magnus (b. 1989) is an Australian actor and comedian. You might have caught her on the very funny Paula Pell vehicle "Mapleworth Murders," which was sentenced to obscurity by its initial run on Quibi (R.I.P.) and current home on the Roku Channel. (Magnus, tall and thin, and Pell, short and round, look like the number 10 solving mysteries in a small town.) She also had roles in the Syfy miniseries "Childhood's End" and the 2015 Kate Winslet film The Dressmaker. She reads a lot of books and just generally seems like a smart cookie.

The most noteworthy thing about Magnus' appearance is her extraordinary limbs. They are longer than limbs have any business being, if we're being honest. If she was an NBA draft pick, the analysts would never shut up about her "length" and "wingspan." People tweet about her: "This lady who plays Heidi on #MapleworthMurders has the longest arms I’ve ever seen?" She has a wikiFeet page that should really be a wikiLimbs page. I believe this embedding has captured said limbs.

This embedding is based on 30 images, cooked for a total of 300 steps on base SD1.5: 16 vectors per token, a 0.004 learning rate, a batch size of 6, and 5 gradient steps.
